Data_type.0: ect-rept-sci-L3>ECT REPT - Relativistic Electron Proton Telescope, Level 3 science data

Logical_source_description.0: RBSP/ECT REPT Monthly Intensities as a function of Energy, Pitch Angle and L-shell from the Selesnick model

TITLE.0: REPT (Relativistic Electron Proton Telescope), Level 3 Selesnick model

TEXT.0: The files contain model radiation belt proton intensity derived from data taken by the Van Allen Probes REPT instruments using the method described by: Selesnick, R. S., Baker, D. N., Kanekal, S. G., Hoxie, V. C., & Li, X. (2018).  Modeling the proton radiation belt with Van Allen Probes Relativistic Electron-Proton Telescope data. Journal of Geophysical Research: Space Physics, 123. https://doi.org/10.1002/2017JA024661 Each file contains average intensity, as a function of kinetic energy, equatorial pitch angle, and L-shell, derived from 1 month of data.

Source_name.0: RBSP>Van Allen Probes, Radiation Belt Storm

Acknowledgement.0: This work was supported by Van Allen Probes/RBSP-ECT funding provided by JHU/APL Contract No. 967399 under NASA's Prime Contract No. NAS5-01072.

LINK_TEXT.0: Modeling the proton radiation belt with Van Allen Probes Relativistic Electron-Proton Telescope data
